# Rule 36 (UNDOCUMENTED_RITE_VAR) — pre-existing undocumented RITE_* variable exemptions
#
# Count frozen at 101 entries as of 2026-07-14.
# DO NOT add new entries — new vars must be documented in:
#   config/project.conf.example  (per-project config vars)
#   config/rite.conf.example     (global operator vars, e.g. model vars)
# or suppressed inline with a Reason:
#   # sharkrite-lint disable UNDOCUMENTED_RITE_VAR - Reason: ...
#
# These are internal implementation vars that pre-date the documentation
# requirement. Burn-down is separate follow-up work.
# Seeded mechanically on 2026-07-14 via:
#   grep -rhoE '\$\{?RITE_[A-Z0-9_]+' lib/ | tr -d '${' | sort -u \
#     | comm -23 - <(grep -hoE 'RITE_[A-Z0-9_]+' \
#         config/project.conf.example config/rite.conf.example | sort -u)
